snippet.textDisplay:
Ok so if Jeffrey’s video was a completely fake then fine. I understand that he kept the car. Slow content day, it happens. I’m a bit surprised there would be legal proceedings if it was a 100% clear to Nate that this wasn’t a present though. But who knows. Breakups are hard and people are capable of anything when hurt !

However, if it was a gift then I don’t agree with Jeffrey. Even if the car was in his name. And even if he is hurt by whatever is happening behind the scenes. A gift is a gift. To me you shouldn’t « gift » anything to someone you’re gonna want back when they break your heart. Even if your the bread winner in that couple. That’s extremely immature to me. In French there’s a saying that goes : giving is giving, taking it back is stealing.
You’re not actually ever gifting your significant other with anything if everything comes with a « if you leave me you loose it all » condition. That’s not a gift. That’s a loan, a treat. And it just seems like a really unhealthy/manipulative dynamic in my opinion: « I’m the breadwinner so you live by my rules » kind of a thing. A very oppressive 50s mentality. If you don’t feel like giving a present to someone no matter what happens between you after then it was never a present in the first place.
Again, i don’t know if this is actually what happened or if Jeffrey is saying the truth about it being 100% fake. Only Jeffrey and Nate know.
